<@U0HPGQ4KH> based on our discussion about 3d cutaway ‘sneak peak’ here is the inspiration I’m working with.  Please also refer to my bullets above (12:57pm 9/22)

Roof: greenery, some nice plants.  Skinny trees.  Some kind of deck with an awning or low-fi covering.  Some picnic tables.  

Fl 3: Think open-office plan.  desks, offices, coffee area where people can congregate.  Boards rooms.  Think about a space, not far from what 811 looks like.  A place designers would like to work. Biz casual but skews more casual.  

Fl 2: laser and 3d printers, separate from cnc mills and waterjet cutter and lathe.

This floor is trickiest for me to conceptualize right now.  Will leave  it as ‘the middle ground’ for you to find as you put yourself into this mindset.

Fl1: Think about hallway to freight elevator.  Think about a little reception desk.  A space for package design and shipping.  Maybe some a coffee roaster (homage to Coava or this building’s history if not literal).  Think about what you’d want someone to see if we were to open one of the garage doors.  

Out front, lets show movement.  The vibrancy of the area.  Maybe a Google Streetview car or something that represents technology.  That or a truck mean too ship/receive something.
